What is Route 53?
AWS DNS service.

Converts domain names into IP addresses.

Example:
User enters:
amazon.com

DNS resolves:
54.x.x.x

Browser reaches server.

Routing Policies:

Simple Routing
Single resource.

Weighted Routing
Traffic split.

Example:
80% → Server A
20% → Server B

Failover Routing:
Primary and backup systems.

Real-Time Scenario:

Global Application

India Users
      ↓
Mumbai Region

US Users
      ↓
Virginia Region

Route 53 directs users to nearest available application.
